description: Where to put utilities — lib vs components
alwaysApply: true
---

# Utility placement

- **`src/lib/<domain>/`** — domain logic with no CSS/JSX ownership: stores, persistence, imaging I/O, hydrate/loaders, geometry, story export/import, deck data→layers, reusable domain hooks.
- **`src/components/...`** — React surfaces only. UI-only helpers used by one component live **in that `.tsx` file**. Do not add sibling `.ts` util modules under `components/`. If a helper gains a second consumer or is non-UI domain logic, move it to `lib/`.
- **`src/player/`** — CDN bootstrap only (`entry.tsx`); no domain growth.
- **No lib → components imports** except static assets (e.g. SVG URLs). Prefer `src/assets` or `src/lib/...` if shared assets grow.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — sibling util under components/
// src/components/shared/channel/contrastScale.ts

// ✅ GOOD — domain I/O in lib/
// src/lib/story/loadStoryDocument.ts

// ✅ GOOD — UI helper in the owning component
// src/components/shared/channel/ChannelContrastEditor.tsx
function buildContrastScale(...) { ... }
```
